subject: Add user_name and project_name to context object
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2472, 'name': 'Doug Hellmann', 'email': 'dhellmann@redhat.com', 'username': 'doug-hellmann'}, {'_account_id': 6854, 'name': 'YAMAMOTO Takashi', 'email': 'yamamoto@midokura.com', 'username': 'yamamoto'}, {'_account_id': 9656, 'name': 'Ihar Hrachyshka', 'email': 'ihrachys@redhat.com', 'username': 'ihrachys', 'status': 'Red Hat Networking Systems Engineer'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-04-22 14:36:15.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_context/tests/test_context.py', 'oslo_context/context.py'], 'message': 'Add user_name and project_name to context object

Also use those attributes to construct user_identity if they are
present.

Devstack currently overrides default logging_context_format_string for
neutron and nova to replace user-id and project-id with something more
user friendly (user and project names) [1][2].

This behaviour should be the default, so that we can avoid overriding
default oslo.log format string while providing users the best user
experience.

Not overwriting default format strings would avoid bugs like [3].

[1]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/nova#n460
[2]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/neutron-legacy#n891
[3]: https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1433687

Related-Bug: #1433687
Change-Id: I2fe05f727743c5d9d1dbf5c5f2b3b0bfd6397f1b
'}]
commit_message:
Add user_name and project_name to context object

Also use those attributes to construct user_identity if they are
present.

Devstack currently overrides default logging_context_format_string for
neutron and nova to replace user-id and project-id with something more
user friendly (user and project names) [1][2].

This behaviour should be the default, so that we can avoid overriding
default oslo.log format string while providing users the best user
experience.

Not overwriting default format strings would avoid bugs like [3].

[1]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/nova#n460
[2]: http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-dev/devstack/tree/lib/neutron-legacy#n891
[3]: https://bugs.launchpad.net/neutron/+bug/1433687

Related-Bug: #1433687
Change-Id: I2fe05f727743c5d9d1dbf5c5f2b3b0bfd6397f1b

commit_message:
Remove unused imported config option causing UT fails

The osapi_v3 group as been deprecated, for which reason the unit
tests fail in our case ATM.

We can simply skip importing this config option as it's unused.

commit_message:
Add a blank line to the beginning of each filter

Filters fragments leads to section headers and previous options with no
blank line between them

  foo = bar
  [section]

Add a blank line to the beginning of each filter so that when applied
the resulting file is more human readable

Change-Id: I411eba5da5fc4e1a7217df197edbaf5ef2d5e4fa

This global variable was initially introduced here:
ff837025e955799e69eebcab665374436649d6f8 and has been copied all
around the code with KLASS instead of CLASS which always made

commit_message:
Rename KLASS -> CLASS in code base

This global variable was initially introduced here:
ff837025e955799e69eebcab665374436649d6f8 and has been copied all
around the code with KLASS instead of CLASS which always made
me wonder why it's called KLASS everytime I see this. Now I
no longer have to see it and wonder :)

find . -name "*py" -print | xargs sed -i 's/KLASS/CLASS/g'

Change-Id: If38720b87c684037ee9ac8b337f9580bb30b30fd

commit_message:
compute: Split the rebuild_instance method

We use a similar pattern we see in other methods especially the
build_and_run_instances, where we move all the logic to a sub-method
as the exception handling around failure to claim resources may get
complicated, so having complex logic inside a try-with construct becomes
difficult to read quickly.

Change-Id: Ia1361e14e6e7a80c404db43a96db7b031a484a55
Related-blueprint: migration-fix-resource-tracking

commit_message:
Catch update to a non-existent artifact property

Currently if an artifact tries to update a property that does not
exist it throws an AttributeError causing a 500. This catches that
exception and causes a ArtifactInvalidProperty returning a 400 error.
Alerting the user that the property does not exist.

FastTrack

Change-Id: I49a385f124236b22360ee07f5adcba27b3c92603
Closes-bug: 1468806

commit_message:
Fix EC GET backend stream iteration state

In EC case, When GET object requested, proxy-server always makes a log
line "Client disconnected on read" even though the request succeeded.

That is because ECAppIter class doesn't maintain a bunch of backend
stream when closing the app_iter. It will cause unfortunately
GeneratorExit on backend stream ResumingGetter.

This patch fixes to set non_client_disconnected to propagate the state
to the backend streams when the range iteration stopped successful.

Co-Authored-By: Clay Gerrard <clay.gerrard@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I77af9807816bea1444d66534a17e2a210bcf09f8
Closes-Bug: #1472201

commit_message:
api: deprecate the concept of extensions in v2.1

We want to remove the extension infrastructure in the v2.1 API during
the next release. To make that possible, we must deprecate the
configuration now.

Also deprecating the osapi_v3 group, and moving to osapi_v21.

UpgradeImpact
DocImpact

Part of blueprint nova-api-deprecate-extensions

Change-Id: I084444b11dceda7cf8f88c157aa67d36490fce49

commit_message:
Splitting stackforge/freezer on multiple repos

The main freezer repo now contains the API and Web UI
code. As the project is growing we would like to have
an individual repo for each component.

This commit refer to the creation of a new freezer-web-ui repo.
The directory horizon_web_ui of the stackforge/freezer repo
needs to be imported on this new repo with the history.

Implements blueprint: main-repo-split

Change-Id: I2e7ea83247eec090f404f66575c9d7b8e19fa894

commit_message:
Add timeout validation for server creation

This patch adds validation to the profile content -- timeout. The value
of 'timeout' must be lower than the 'default_action_timeout', or else
the profile operations will fail for sure.

Change-Id: I9903a60db3f778e8698de6872eabb31465244e2c

the Heat container with a heat domain user.  This requires some
work from bootstrap.yml to pass in several environment variables
needed by the heat domain setup script.

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-08-31 10:08:54.000000000', 'files': ['bootstrap/sync/etc/e2fsck.conf', 'fuel-bootstrap-image-builder/share/fuel-bootstrap-image/ubuntu/files/etc/e2fsck.conf'], 'message': 'Fix file system mount in the future

The issue is that when image is built and immediately
copied to a slave node and if the slave node is not
synchronized with master node, we can encounter

"Superblock last write time is in the future."

And then e2fsck returns exit code 1 which leads

e2fsck option fixes the issue. Unfortunately,

Change-Id: If8db3c1b09521d4093fdc928d595240928e92e49

commit_message:
Fix file system mount in the future

The issue is that when image is built and immediately
copied to a slave node and if the slave node is not
synchronized with master node, we can encounter
the following error when running e2fsck

"Superblock last write time is in the future."

And then e2fsck returns exit code 1 which leads
fuel agent to fail. "broken_system_clock = true"
e2fsck option fixes the issue. Unfortunately,
this option can not be passed to e2fsck
as a CLI option (only via global config).

Another possible solution would be to artificially
set image timestamps into, for example, Jan 1 1970.

Change-Id: If8db3c1b09521d4093fdc928d595240928e92e49
Closes-Bug: #1489475
Co-Authored-By: Alexey Sheplyakov <asheplyakov@mirantis.com>
